<UserControl
    xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
    xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
	xmlns:shared="http://schemas.actiprosoftware.com/winfx/xaml/shared" 
	xmlns:editor="http://schemas.actiprosoftware.com/winfx/xaml/syntaxeditor" 
	xmlns:editors="http://schemas.actiprosoftware.com/winfx/xaml/editors" 
	xmlns:sample="clr-namespace:ActiproSoftware.ProductSamples.SyntaxEditorSamples.QuickStart.AdornmentsSmokeText"
    >

	<editor:SyntaxEditor x:Name="editor">
			<editor:EditorDocument x:Name="document" xml:space="preserve">
				<editor:EditorDocument.Language>
					<sample:CustomSyntaxLanguage />
				</editor:EditorDocument.Language><![CDATA[This QuickStart shows how to create an adornment manager that creates
a smoke text special effect as text is changed within an editor view.

The adornment manager is created by the syntax language assigned to
this editor's document.  It shows how to only show smoke effects
in the active view.

To see the effect in action, start typing and changing text in this
view.
]]></editor:EditorDocument>
	</editor:SyntaxEditor>
	
</UserControl>
